column3: The former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia
The former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia
Percentage of women aged 15–49 years attended at least once during pregnancy by skilled health personnel (doctor, nurse or midwife).
The indicator refers to women who had a live birth in a recent time period, generally two years for MICS and five years for DHS.
Database include reanalyzed data from DHS and MICS, using a reference period of two years before the survey.
Includes surveys which microdata were available as of April 2016.
UNICEF global databases 2016 based on DHS, MICS .
